# Database Layer: TypeORM is the Standard

All NestJS services in ZoneVast use **TypeORM** as the ORM. Do NOT introduce Prisma, Drizzle, Kysely, or any other ORM.

## NestJS Services Using TypeORM

| Service | TypeORM Version |
|---|---|
| `auction-service` | ^0.3.28 |
| `zv-flex-auth-service` | ^0.3.19 |
| `auth-nestjs` | ^0.3.19 |
| `nestjs-common-layer` | ^0.3.19 |

## Why TypeORM Over Prisma

- **Lambda deployment size**: TypeORM ~5MB vs Prisma ~30-50MB (binary engine)
- **Cold start speed**: TypeORM is pure JS, Prisma requires engine initialization
- **NestJS integration**: `@nestjs/typeorm` provides first-class integration (decorators, modules, guards)
- **Complex queries**: `createQueryBuilder` handles joins, aggregations, and raw SQL gracefully
- **Shared infrastructure**: `nestjs-common-layer` Lambda layer already bundles TypeORM
- **Multi-schema PostgreSQL**: TypeORM handles `DB_SCHEMA` properly, Prisma has limited support

## Usage Patterns

### Repository Pattern (Simple CRUD)
```typescript
@InjectRepository(Auction)
private readonly auctionRepository: Repository<Auction>;

// Create
const auction = this.auctionRepository.create({ title, startPrice });
await this.auctionRepository.save(auction);

// Read
await this.auctionRepository.findOne({ where: { id } });

// Update
await this.auctionRepository.update(id, { status: 'active' });

// Delete (soft)
await this.auctionRepository.softRemove(auction);
```

### QueryBuilder (Complex Queries)
```typescript
this.auctionRepository
  .createQueryBuilder('auction')
  .where('auction.projectId = :projectId', { projectId })
  .andWhere('auction.title ILIKE :search', { search: `%${term}%` })
  .orderBy('auction.createdAt', 'DESC')
  .skip((page - 1) * limit)
  .take(limit)
  .getManyAndCount();
```

### Raw Queries via Manager (Cross-Entity)
```typescript
this.auctionRepository.manager
  .createQueryBuilder()
  .select('COUNT(*)', 'count')
  .from('bids', 'bid')
  .where('bid.created_at > :date', { date: oneHourAgo })
  .getRawOne();
```

## Security Rules

- Always use parameterized queries (`:paramName` or `$1, $2`)
- Never concatenate user input into SQL strings
- Validate `sortBy` fields against a whitelist before using in `orderBy`
- Use `class-validator` decorators on all DTOs
- Set `whitelist: true` and `forbidNonWhitelisted: true` on `ValidationPipe`
